$interpreted: Hyacinthus: Lio! So you're back!
Hyacinthus: Did you give Leah all the clothes we prepared for her?
Hyacinthus: Did she tell you a date she's coming back to visit us?
Lio: Sis said she's too busy to come back and told me not to visit her if there's nothing urgent.
Lio: So, so...
Nigel: So you guys had an argument?
Lio: Yes...
Lio: I said a lot of mean things to sis... She's definitely mad right now...
Lio: If... If sis really decides to never come back again...
Nigel: Then instead of wasting time here crying like a wimp, you should be finding a way to apologize and make up with her instead.
Lio: But, how am I supposed to make up with sis...
Hyacinthus: Hmm... I remember when you and Leah were little,
Hyacinthus: as long as you two had some tasty food, you would instantly forget anything unpleasant!
Lio: But, tasty food isn't exactly something you find in the Slums...
Nigel: Alright then, I'll take you on a trip to Maple Lake next time. The water there is sparkling clean, so the fruits and vegetables nearby are all top-notch.
Lio: Maple Lake...
Nigel: The Slums has been a bit chaotic over the past few days. Once everything has settled down, I'll take you there...
Nigel: Hey! Where did he go?
Nigel: Lio! Didn't I tell you not to wander around yourself!

Lio: Nigel, the fruits and vegetables you mentioned...
are they around these lake shores?
Nigel: I do recall that there's a Pomelodora farm somewhere around here...
Lio: Pomelodora?  What is that?
Nigel: It's a green fruit that grows underground. It smells nice and has a sweet flavor. It's quite delicious.
Nigel: However, this area is very dangerous. Wait for me here. I'll search for it along the shores. Do NOT wander around!
Lio: I guess I should take a look around here as well...
Lio: Hmm? What is that?
Lio: A green fruit... Is this the Pomelodora Nigel was talking about?
Lio: Hehe~ Once sis eats this tasty fruit, she probably won't be mad at me anymore!
Lio: Oh, I should pick a few more for Nigel and Cin too!
